# Skrya Full

Injected into a `{{HOST_NAME}}` coding session for substantial work in this repository.

## Full Pipeline

1. Read `{{INSTRUCTION_FILE}}`, `README.md`, `design/current-system-design.md`, and `design/core-skills-spec.md`.
2. Treat `skill-pack.json`, `SKILL.md.tmpl`, the root skill directories, and `prompt-templates/` as the source of truth for agent-facing assets.
3. If the request concerns unconfigured ongoing tracking, route through `topic-curation` before digest or deep-analysis behavior.
4. If the user asks for a scheduled topical news push, such as "每天早上8点推送国内外 X 的官媒信息和新闻", treat it as Skrya topic setup before generic automation.
5. For ongoing tracking requests, distinguish them from one-off research, handle recurring automation or scheduling before any digest output, and ask whether the user wants a test run instead of running one automatically.
6. After the user confirms a new or expanded topic scope, require source candidate confirmation before saying it is connected or creating recurring automation.
7. Source candidate confirmation must consider configured retrieval/source channels such as X and WeChat official accounts when available, not just generic web/news search.
8. After sources and recurring delivery are configured, proactively ask whether to run one test digest now.
9. Installation is language-neutral. Infer each topic's output language from topic creation or explicit user preference; currently support Chinese and English output while keeping the schema extensible.
10. Test runs must use the formal digest template, include the topic-language system section (`## 系统提示` or `## System`), explain A/B/C follow-ups, and avoid saving `latest-digest.md` unless explicitly requested.
10. When the host is channel-aware, bind recurring digest delivery to the creating user and current channel/conversation by default; do not resend or combine digests from other channels unless explicitly requested and supported.
11. When improving recall, update the smallest relevant persistent instruction surface when allowed, such as `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `tools.md`, or documented global memory.
12. Resolve the Skrya data root before topic-scoped work; use `~/.skrya` by default and workspace `.skrya/data` when the host or container mount requires workspace-local state.
13. When skill or prompt behavior changes, regenerate the installable skill pack with `python -m skrya_orchestrator.main build-skill-pack --root . --host all`.
14. Update tests and docs together with the behavior change.
15. Before finishing, run the full unittest suite and report the verification result.

